Date Reviewed: 22/10/07 andrewjaprice Member Since: 21/09/07
View Member's: Reviews After much research into LCD televisions (this is my first) I decided on the Samsung LE32R87BDX. After searching around I bought through Micro Supermarket, as a friend recommended it to me. I ordered the TV midday on Thursday and it was delivered the next day, which needless to say I was very pleased with. Having now installed the TV. Its really is all that it is cracked up to be. The picture is exceptionally clear. Its a great looking set, has a fantastic specification and is easy to use. There are slight negative features of the television such as the speed at which channels change. But in my opinion they are far out waded by the positives and overall value. Overall Rating
